1
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:23,260
♪Wandering alone♪

2
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:25,540
♪Walking far by dusk-lit streets♪

3
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:27,430
♪Your eyes are as cold as clouds♪

4
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:28,970
♪Faintly coming into view♪

5
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:30,360
♪The city lights♪

6
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,630
♪Lit up that single moment♪

7
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:36,140
♪I can't hide or stop missing you♪

8
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:37,640
♪I can't forget those moments♪

9
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:39,280
♪Losing you♪

10
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Like the seasons in my memory♪

11
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,290
♪Without winter♪

12
00:00:43,290 --> 00:00:44,920
♪Walking down the long, dark street♪

13
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,460
♪Snow will never fall again♪

14
00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:48,200
♪Our old story was torn♪

15
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,610
♪Into scattered pieces♪

16
00:00:50,610 --> 00:00:53,430
♪Replaying every single scene♪

17
00:00:53,430 --> 00:00:55,980
♪After you left♪

18
00:00:57,530 --> 00:01:00,510
♪As if our documentary♪

19
00:01:00,510 --> 00:01:03,120
♪Lost winter♪

20
00:01:04,770 --> 00:01:07,180
♪The breeze speaks of good times♪

21
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:11,080
♪Pure white devotion♪

22
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,990
♪Send out a letter♪

23
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:17,780
♪Carrying my longing♪

24
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,980
=The Double Game=

25
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 10=

26
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:47,610
Sis,

27
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,560
being here reminds me

28
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,870
that on my birthday, we booked tons...

29
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:58,310
We invited a bunch of friends over.

30
00:02:01,870 --> 00:02:02,710
Right.

31
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,000
Now I remember.

32
00:02:04,150 --> 00:02:04,990
This is the place.

33
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,280
Among your friends,

34
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,030
there was one named Xiao Ting.

35
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,150
Interesting name.

36
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,810
- Good physique too.
- Well.

37
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,560
I even thought it was you.

38
00:02:17,150 --> 00:02:17,990
No way.

39
00:02:18,260 --> 00:02:19,130
Think about how

40
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:20,630
to set up your new office.

41
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,120
Wait.

42
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:29,910
Are you sure the office is here?

43
00:02:31,430 --> 00:02:32,270
Don't worry.

44
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,520
I've had Bai set it all up.

45
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,190
I've told you all I know.

46
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,310
The Lianxin Island site

47
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,840
was secured by Lin Youqiang.

48
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,080
He also oversaw the reclamation.

49
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,360
As for the improper procedures

50
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:51,870
you just mentioned,

51
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:53,960
I only just found out myself.

52
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,400
If you need more details,

53
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:58,750
you can ask him.

54
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:01,150
Call him.

55
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:02,270
Okay.

56
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:11,590
Lin Youqiang...

57
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:27,360
Sis, do you know this guy?

58
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,786
Does he have a girlfriend?

59
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,910
This is my childhood buddy, Bai.

60
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,520
Single since birth.

61
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,640
Okay.

62
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,630
Wow, this place is nice.

63
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,470
How'd you get the club owner

64
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:48,240
to clear out a spot
in a place that makes

65
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:49,680
millions a day for my studio?

66
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,030
Well.

67
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,750
You'll have to ask the owner.

68
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:57,280
This is your business too?

69
00:03:59,206 --> 00:04:00,120
Security's solid here.

70
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,190
My office is right outside.

71
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:04,800
I'll worry less with you here.

72
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,190
If you want more privacy,

73
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:09,000
use the back entrance.

74
00:04:09,376 --> 00:04:10,520
I'll have Bai give you a key.

75
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:14,750
That's so thoughtful.

76
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,030
Sis,

77
00:04:17,114 --> 00:04:18,383
I want him as my brother-in-law.

78
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,200
Bai,

79
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,600
this place is so cool.

80
00:04:27,950 --> 00:04:29,360
Can you show me around?

81
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:30,350
I'd like to see it.

82
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,650
Okay.

83
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,520
Let's go.

84
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,000
Okay.

85
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,750
Why did you bring this too?

86
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,480
How did you know I like it?

87
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,000
Elephants are

88
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,240
in your videos and logo.

89
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:57,120
So, it must mean a lot to you.

90
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,520
But

91
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,240
why do you like elephants?

92
00:05:04,390 --> 00:05:06,680
Because elephants are the smartest,

93
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:08,030
just like me.

94
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,200
Well.

95
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:21,360
Actually,

96
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:24,270
it's because elephants live in herds.

97
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,070
They have strong family bonds.

98
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:30,040
I grew up in an orphanage.

99
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,270
I never knew who my family was

100
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,440
or where they were.

101
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,870
Only on our birthdays could we

102
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:38,920
ask for a gift.

103
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:42,190
Every year,
I'd ask for an elephant plushie.

104
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,800
They couldn't talk,

105
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,120
but they stayed with me like family.

106
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,830
I still keep up that tradition.

107
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:03,240
These elephants

108
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:10,720
have kind of grown up with me.

109
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,320
You won't be

110
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:25,830
alone anymore.

111
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,400
Honestly,

112
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,430
you're like an elephant too.

113
00:06:46,769 --> 00:06:48,075
You have a sharp sense of smell.

114
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:50,480
You catch anything unusual.

115
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,593
You're also sharp-tongued

116
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,800
and fierce

117
00:06:58,950 --> 00:06:59,870
like an elephant.

118
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:23,720
Lu Jianchuan's likely being questioned.

119
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:26,910
Congrats, Mr. Lu.

120
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:29,830
You're closer to owning Luzhou Group.

121
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:38,510
I'll go in first in a bit.

122
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:39,870
You come later.

123
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:42,910
Why?

124
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:44,110
Afraid they'll think

125
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,680
we look too good together?

126
00:07:46,950 --> 00:07:48,270
What are you saying?

127
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,840
Zhi'er, you're back.

128
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,160
(Why hasn't that old man been arrested?)

129
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:17,030
- Zhi'er, come here.
- Zhi'er.

130
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,830
Dad, Mom.

131
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:21,150
Zhi'er,

132
00:08:21,630 --> 00:08:22,950
something this big happened,

133
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,830
and you didn't tell us at all?

134
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,680
Your father-in-law and I
were worried sick

135
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:29,560
that you'd do something rash.

136
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,480
What happened?

137
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:35,480
You still don't know?

138
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:40,030
Take a look yourself.

139
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,550
The police are investigating Youqiang.

140
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:50,790
(Lin Youqiang died in crash)

141
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:52,390
For some reason,

142
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,240
he ran with his family

143
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,630
and had an accident on the way.

144
00:08:58,510 --> 00:08:59,960
Fate can be so cruel.

145
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:02,560
Yeah.

146
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,030
Your parents died suddenly.

147
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:06,550
We were heartbroken too.

148
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:08,510
But

149
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:11,960
you're your father's only child alive.

150
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,280
So,

151
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,870
all your father's final arrangements

152
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:17,550
may fall on you alone.

153
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:19,590
Zhi'er,

154
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:23,080
Linhai Group is a huge operation.

155
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,910
You're the only blood heir.

156
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,030
Inside and out,

157
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,000
a lot of people are watching.

158
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,040
Don't worry.

159
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,600
I'll help you hold this together.

160
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,530
Yeah.

161
00:09:36,550 --> 00:09:38,360
If anything's wrong, tell me.

162
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,240
I'll have your husband come back

163
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,260
and stay with you now.

164
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,550
You can have him do whatever you want.

165
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,560
Zhi'er.

166
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,440
Zhi'er?

167
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,440
Mom.

168
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,480
I need a moment to calm down.

169
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,360
Okay, okay. Go get some rest.

170
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,630
You know, Lin Zhi'er

171
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,440
really is pretty lucky.

172
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:13,080
Now, she's the Lin family's only heir.

173
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:16,360
If it weren't for her shares,

174
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:19,440
who'd bother sucking up to her?

175
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:21,870
Think of the bigger picture.

176
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:24,270
I know.

177
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:27,440
To help you control Linhai Group,

178
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,550
I'll put up with whatever it takes

179
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,080
and keep her happy for you.

180
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,750
(Lin Youqiang,)

181
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,515
(you wanted Lu Jianchuan's trust)

182
00:10:37,526 --> 00:10:38,910
(before you died.)

183
00:10:39,510 --> 00:10:41,150
(Look at him setting you up.)

184
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,280
Still,

185
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,480
that said,

186
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:50,000
our group has had

187
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,750
one issue after another lately.

188
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,840
The financial scandal,

189
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,510
the land reclamation scandal,

190
00:10:56,910 --> 00:11:00,200
and now these construction violations.

191
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,320
With one setback after another,

192
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,150
I am still very worried.

193
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,870
But it seems

194
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,870
all this started
after Tingxiao came back.

195
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,630
Let's hope you're overthinking it.

196
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,750
If Tingxiao really is
pulling strings behind our backs,

197
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:32,150
I won't spare him

198
00:11:32,790 --> 00:11:34,440
for being my son.

199
00:11:39,630 --> 00:11:40,470
(Email)
Lin Zhi'er,

200
00:11:40,630 --> 00:11:41,630
Lin Youqiang has died.

201
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,166
Come back for the funeral.

202
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,510
♪This door♪

203
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:09,660
♪Lets in the sky outside♪

204
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:13,700
♪With a voice even lighter♪

205
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:16,510
♪Than how you just greeted me♪

206
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,330
♪I know now♪

207
00:12:18,660 --> 00:12:23,540
♪What the chill in my body means♪

208
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:26,760
♪The moment salt hits the wound♪

209
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:30,380
♪My heart still beats so naively♪

210
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:33,540
♪To complete♪

211
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:37,750
♪A joy that needs no brave pretense♪

212
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:40,390
♪How cruel sincerity can be♪

213
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:44,080
♪Like a door with no key♪

214
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:46,710
♪Maybe you just passed by♪

215
00:12:46,710 --> 00:12:50,290
♪The tears in my eyes♪

216
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,550
♪You looked like you had nothing to say♪

217
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:55,290
♪Then got so good at being cold♪

218
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:58,130
♪That's why a smile feels so precious♪

219
00:12:58,340 --> 00:13:00,430
♪Maybe you just passed by♪

220
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:04,910
♪The tears burned into my heart♪

221
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:07,580
♪Let's say silence was just for show♪

222
00:13:07,580 --> 00:13:12,250
♪Even if I've grown another year♪
